                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d207">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/34<hi rend="superscript"
                    >10/12</hi>: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-09-10T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >September 10, 1940—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>138. Staff conversations were begun this afternoon with the Minister of Foreign
                    Relations and myself present. General views were <pb facs="0173" n="161"
                        xml:id="pg_161"/> exchanged and an analysis of the agenda of both services
                    was presented orally and in writing for the information of the Ministers of War
                    and Marine. The next meeting will take place Friday when the Peruvians will have
                    their data prepared for discussion of specific subjects.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Norweb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
